In [194]:
#Treating with Outliers

#insulin

limit_1 = data['Insulin'].quantile(0.25)
limit_3 = data['Insulin'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = limit_3 - limit_1
lower_limit = limit_1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_limit = limit_3 + 1.5 * IQR

data = data[(data['Insulin'] > lower_limit) & (data['Insulin'] < upper_limit)]

In [201]:
#outcome

data_majority = data[(data["Outcome"]==0)]
data_minority = data[(data["Outcome"]==1)]
data_minority_upsampled = resample(data_minority,replace=True,n_samples=500,random_state=42)
data = pd.concat([data_minority_upsampled,data_majority])
In [202]:
#Splitting the data and feature Scaling

X=data.drop('Outcome',axis='columns')
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaler.fit_transform(X)
Y=data["Outcome"]
X_train,X_test,Y_train,Y_test=train_test_split(X,Y,test_size=0.10)
In [203]:
#Random Forest Regression
model_1 = RandomForestClassifier()
model_1.fit(X_train,Y_train)
model_1.score(X_test,Y_test)
cm = confusion_matrix(Y_test,model_1.predict(X_test))
cr=classification_report(Y_test, model_1.predict(X_test))
print(cm)
print(cr)

sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=".0f",color="white")
plt.xlabel('y_pred')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.show()

#Support vector machine with grid search CV


from sklearn.svm import SVC
svc = SVC(class_weight='balanced')
param_grid_svc = {'C':[0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 0.5, 1],'gamma':['scale', 'auto']}
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
model_4 = GridSearchCV(svc, param_grid=param_grid_svc)
model_4.fit(X_train,Y_train);
model_4.best_params_
svc_pred = model_4.predict(X_test)
accuracy_score(Y_test,svc_pred)
cr=classification_report(Y_test,svc_pred)
print(cr)
cm = confusion_matrix(Y_test,model_4.predict(X_test))
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=".0f")
plt.xlabel('y_pred')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.show()
